!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

sob /sɒb/

(sobbing,sobbed,sobs) 

1. V-I When someone sobs , they cry in a noisy way, breathing in short breaths. 抽噎 

例： She began to sob again, burying her face in the pillow. 她又开始抽噎，把脸埋在枕头里。 

2. sobbing N-UNCOUNT 抽噎 

例： The room was silent except for her sobbing. 房间里除了她的啜泣声一片寂静。 

3. N-COUNT A sob is one of the noises that you make when you are crying. 呜咽声 

例： Her sobs grew louder. 她的呜咽声变得更大了。

